# 副簽
(pos: 名詞)
<explanation>
yue: 喺文件、合約或公文上，由主要簽署人以外嘅人（通常係副手或相關負責人）加簽嘅名或簽名，用以表示知悉、同意或共同負責（量詞：個）
eng: countersignature; secondary signature
<eg>
yue: 份合約要等經理簽咗先，仲要副簽先算生效。 (fan5 ho4 yiu5 yiu5 dang2 ging1 li5 hin1 zo2 sin1, zung1 yiu5 fu3 hin1 sin1 soeng2 sing6 faat3.)
eng:The contract only becomes effective after the manager signs it and it is countersigned.

yue: 呢張單嘅副簽係由會計部嘅主管負責。 (ni1 zoeng1 daan1 ge3 fu3 hin1 hai6 jau6 keoi4 gei3 bou6 ge3 zyu3 gwaan1 fu5 zek3.)
eng:The countersignature on this form is handled by the supervisor of the accounting department. [end of text]


